added.title: The Titans Show
added.description: The Titans try to get off the desert island but soon realize everything is not as it seems.

added.title: That's What's Up
added.description: Beast Boy heads back east to visit his family, the Doom Patrol, and they decide to throw a clambake to celebrate.

added.title: Crab Shenanigans
added.description: Beast Boy, Negative Girl, and Robotman start hanging out with some punk crabs but soon discover the crabs are up to no good.

added.title: Brobots
added.description: Cyborg comes to visit Beast Boy, but once Cyborg realizes how much he and Robotman have in common, they become inseparable.

added.title: Brain Flip
added.description: It's time for Beast Boy to leave, but the Doom Patrol try everything they can to get him to stay.

added.title: The Fight
added.description: Anais is convinced that Gumball is being bullied by Tina Rex.

added.title: The Authority
added.description: Granny JoJo's overprotective behavior puts the Wattersons in danger...from themselves.

added.title: The Knights
added.description: Gumball and Tobias compete for Penny's affection by putting on the lamest duel in history.

added.title: The Castle
added.description: When Mom is away "anything goes" and Dad's lack of rules soon attracts unwelcome houseguests.

added.title: The Outside
added.description: The family goes to visit Richard's Dad. Based on his basic living standards and extended absence from Richard's life, they assume Frankie must have done a stretch in the slammer. When Frankie comes to stay with the Wattersons, they decide the way to make him comfortable is to make him uncomfortable and turn their house into a prison.

added.title: The Kid From 3030
added.description: The kids meet a mysterious kid from the future and try to help him complete his mission.

added.title: Jessica's Trail
added.description: Jessica wanders into an unfamiliar creek, leaving Craig to find her before his Mom notices!

added.title: Summer Wish
added.description: When Craig decides to keep a lightning bug in a jar, he disrupts the delicate balance of Summer.

added.title: The Jump Off
added.description: Craig, Cannonball, Sparkle Cadet and Diane find themselves wrapped up in a double dutch tournament.

added.title: The Cow-Boy and Marie
added.description: A rebellious Cow-Boy moseys into the Horse Girl Meadow, and causes a ruckus in the Creek.

added.title: Hashtag #1 Fan
added.description: Panda gets kidnapped by a pair of deranged French foxes.

added.title: Snow Place Like Home
added.description: When the Bears realize whatever they build with snow comes to life they decide to build the biggest snow party of all time.

added.title: Fiesta Day
added.description: The Bears party it up with a living piñatas for Fiesta Day. Wanting the festivities to never end, Grizz wishes for it to be Fiesta Day everyday.

added.title: Baba Yaga House
added.description: Squatter Otter tries to win Panda's trust and convince the Bears to live in a mysterious house.

added.title: Bears in the Dark
added.description: The Bears search for their missing box in a dark and scary cave.

added.title: Apoca-lice Now
added.description: When Chef brokers a truce with lice by selecting three kids to "host" them on their heads, Courtney instigates a kid vs. lice war.

added.title: Gnome More Mister Nice Guy
added.description: When the daycare gets taken over by evil gnomes, Duncan finds himself on the wrong team.

added.title: Look Who's Clocking
added.description: When Harold's warnings not to mess with the clock go ignored, the kids are forced to save themselves when Duncan tears a hole in the fabric of time.

added.title: Harold Swatter and the Goblet of Flies
added.description: After finding what he believes to be a magic wand, Owen accidentally turns Harold into a housefly.

added.title: Stink. Stank. Stunk
added.description: When a skunk comes seeking its annual revenge on Chef, Duncan sees it as an opportunity to get a vacation from daycare.

added.title: Onionless
added.description: Onion needs to leave town so Apple has to survive the weekend alone while taking care of Onion's beloved plant.

added.title: Party Popper
added.description: Apple and Onion's party plans are interrupted by a grumpy guest.

added.title: Face Your Fears
added.description: Apple and Onion must face their fears if they are to save French Fry from their bad advice.

added.title: Apple's Short
added.description: Apple wants to experience love.

added.title: Positive Attitude Theory
added.description: Apple and Onion spend a day in Falafel's shoes and use their positive attitude to prove he shouldn't be so grumpy.

added.title: My Bodyguard
added.description: When Zombozo hypnotizes Grandpa Max's entire baking class it is up to Ben and Gwen to clean up the mess, but it gets even messier when Zombozo unveils his new bodyguard: Kevin 11!

added.title: Wheels of Fortune
added.description: Team Tennyson's thrift store shopping is ruined by the latest high-speed heist of LaGrange — who is now aided by a super-fast electromagnetic racing car — and Ben must convince Kevin 11 to help stop the speed demon's globetrotting robbing spree.

added.title: Heat of the Moment
added.description: After Ben easily dispatches the Weatherheads, Team Tennyson travels to a ski resort for some fun in the snow but when Ben runs into the Weatherheads yet again, this time they are a force to reckon with, now that Kevin 11 has used his Bootleg powers to unlock their emotional controls!

added.title: Vin Diagram
added.description: When Ben sees Vin Ethanol impressed with Kevin's automotive know-how, Ben's jealousy has him convinced that he has to out-do Kevin before the older boy influences Vin to embrace his bad-guy side at a charity race.

added.title: A Sticky Situation
added.description: All Ben wants to do is stop Queen Bee from robbing a bank, but when Kevin shows up to try and be the hero and take all the glory himself, Ben will need to save the day twice or end up in hot honey.

added.title: It Was Them
added.description: Dr. Animo has escaped his Plumber prison, and Ben and Rook must track him down before he turns the world into his personal mutant ant farm! (Introducing Nemetrix alien Slamworm, Galvan Plumbers Blukic and Driba, Arctiguana, new Ben alien Crashhopper.)

added.title: So Long, and Thanks for All the Smoothies
added.description: When Ben and Rook investigate a mysterious alien ghost ship, they discover that Argit and the Vreedle Brothers are fighting for possession of a doomsday device! (Introducing Solid Plugg.)

added.title: Hot Stretch
added.description: Ben and Rook encounter a race of elastic, hot-blooded aliens in Undertown who want to use a stolen nuclear fusion engine to activate a volcano! (Introducing Ester, Seebik & the Kraaho.)

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 1
added.description: After a heated argument, Ben and Rook go their separate ways, giving Khyber the Huntsman his best chance to capture Ben! (Introducing Dr. Psychobos, new Nemetrix aliens Mucillator & Terroranchula; new Ben alien Ballweevil.)

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 2
added.description: While trapped in Khyber's ship, Ben learns details about the origin of the Nemetrix, and the link between Khyber, Malware, and Dr. Psychobos! (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Tyrannopede.)

added.title: Lucky Girl
added.description: Ben battles an evil sorcerer whose power whose emanates from mystic charms, one of which turns Gwen into her own superhero named Lucky Girl.

added.title: A Small Problem
added.description: When Ben is not allowed on an attraction at a water park because he's too short, he decides to go alien to get even with the ride's attendant.

added.title: Side Effects
added.description: Ben catches a cold and the symptoms wreak havoc on his alien heroes. To make matters even worse, he has to battle a creature made from cockroaches.

added.title: Jakesuit
added.description: Jake is sick and tired of Finn using his body as a suit of armor so he convinces Finn to trade places to show him how much it really stinks.

added.title: Jake the Dad
added.description: Jake's a daddy, but being a father and keeping his rainicorn pups from killing themselves or each other is a lot harder than he imagined.

added.title: Joshua & Margaret Investigations
added.description: Finn and Jake's parents hunt an unearthly menace in the woods.

added.title: The Visitor
added.description: A vision leads Finn to a friendly civilization and a mysterious crash site.

added.title: The Comet
added.description: Finn, Jake and Orgalorg converge with the comet and meet their destiny.

added.title: Unikitty News!
added.description: You're watching the Unikingdom News Show Super Good Morning Time Program Action Information Show, a variety news program put on (badly) by Unikitty and the gang: Hawkodile does the weather, Puppycorn does sports despite knowing none of the rules, Dr. Fox puts on a fun science-y cooking segment that goes awry, and Richard wants this to stop. Unikitty's got some hard hitting reporting and a big scoop after the break, if the studio survives that long!

added.title: Dinner Apart-y
added.description: Unikitty and Puppycorn are invited to Master Frown and Brock's apartment for a dinner party. But the two roommates are butting heads, and are anything but on the same page. Can Unikitty help Brock and Master Frown get back in harmony before the dinner party is ruined? Will Puppycorn figure out which door is the bathroom?

added.title: R & Arr
added.description: It's Lazy Sunday, and Unikitty and Puppycorn are having such an amazing time hanging out on the couch, they never want to move! Richard insists they have chores to do, but they're unwilling to let Lazy Sunday end. The two go to ridiculous lengths to never leave the comfort of their sofa, rowing it across the castle and like a ship and conscripting their friends to abandon their chores and join Lazy Sunday… no matter how dangerous and impossible it might become!

added.title: License to Punch
added.description: Hawkodile's caught by the Action Police for bodyguarding without an Action License. He's can't protect the kingdom or do anything rad until he does, but the test at the DMV (The Department of Mayhem and Violence) is for nerds! Forced to retire his gloves, Hawkodile struggles to live a life without punching, so Unikitty vows to help her friend contain his urge to be action-y and study for the test. But there's more to the test than meets the eye.

added.title: Buggin' Out
added.description: When Unikitty and the gang discover a gross bug in the castle, they desperately want it gone for good, but Unikitty refuses to allow them to squish it, no matter how icky or dangerous looking it is. What sort of web is Unikitty weaving for her friends?

added.title: The Powerpuff Girls: A Documentary/Girls Gone Mild
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls a Documentary: A film student attempts to do a documentary on the Powerpuff Girls and learns catching these superheroes at rest is harder than he thought./Girls Gone Mild: When Parents Against Powerpuffs tell the girls that their superheroics are becoming too imitable, the girls must hold back on fighting crime.

added.title: Monstra-City/Shut the Pup Up
added.description: Monstra-city: When all the monsters move from Monster Isle to Townsville, it's up to the Girls to keep the peace./Shut the Pup Up: When the Talking Dog witnesses a crime, he moves in with the girls for protection. But the girls soon realize this chatterbox dog is less than the perfect pet.

added.title: Lying Around the House/Bubble Boy
added.description: Lying Around The House: The girls tell little white lies that turn into a big, bad problem./Bubble Boy: Realizing that the only way to beat the Rowdyruff Boys is to join them, Bubbles takes Boomer's place in this rough-and-tumble band of boys.

added.title: Power-Noia
added.description: The girls have become paralyzed by their greatest fears. Who could be behind such an evil trick?

added.title: Keen on Keane/Not So Awesome Blossom
added.description: Keen on Keane: It's Valentine's Day and the girls notice that Ms. Keane is all alone. Time for a little matchmaking, but who will be the lucky fella?/Not So Awesome Blossom: When Blossom's attack plans fail one after the other, she loses confidence in herself as the group's leader.

added.title: Take Your Kids to Dooms Day
added.description: The Girls spend the day with the Professor at his boring office, only to find that the office comes with a terrible secret.

added.title: Memory Lane of Pain
added.description: While going through the Professor's scrapbook, Bubbles starts to question if she's ever been a hero.

added.title: Spider Sense
added.description: When a monster ruins their relaxing vacation, the Girls run into a familiar face.

added.title: Imagine That
added.description: The Girls have to battle Him after he causes Bubbles' imagination to run wild.

added.title: Baby Orphan Ninja Bears
added.description: The Baby Bears venture into the sewers and meet a ninja-like martial arts master.

added.title: Fire!
added.description: Grizz's quick thinking prevents a potential wild fire, but the praise he receives from doing so quickly goes to his head.

added.title: Ranger Norm
added.description: When Tabes leaves for a conference, the Bears have to deal with her substitute, Ranger Norm.

added.title: Shmorby
added.description: The Bears get a Shmorby home assistant device and become lazy couch potatoes.

added.title: Snake Babies
added.description: Charlie adopts baby snakes despite the Bears thinking he's not ready for parenthood.

added.title: Leg Wrestler
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and Mr. Gus argue over what show to watch on TV, Pizza Steve has the perfect way to solve their dilemma: Leg wrestling battle!

added.title: Future Pizza
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa travels back through time with a warning that Pizza Steve will do something to offend him in the next five minutes, Pizza Steve begins to obsess over what he could possibly do to offend Uncle Grandpa.

added.title: More Uncle Grandpa Shorts
added.description: Series of shorts starring everyone's favorite uncle and grandpa!

added.title: Viewer Special
added.description: Uncle Grandpa announces the winner of a contest to draw the latest episode of Uncle Grandpa.  Too bad the winner is a metalhead who torments the gang with his strange doodles.

added.title: Bad Morning
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa wakes up on the wrong side of the bed, he changes into a grumpy grump and it's up to the rest of the gang to reverse his bad day.

added.title: Would You Like to Enter Prime Empire?
added.description: While investigating a heist, the ninja discover Prime Empire, a legendary unreleased arcade game that suddenly takes control of all other games in Ninjago.

added.title: Dyer Island
added.description: When the ninja connect Jay's disappearance to Prime Empire, they set out to Dyer Island to seek answers from the game's designer, the elusive Milton Dyer.

added.title: The Ascent
added.description: Cole, the Lowly, Princess Vania and Wu discover that the stone-mech is fueled by Elemental Power, and attach it to the mine-carts in an effort to blast their way out of the mountain to confront the evil Skull Sorcerer!

added.title: The Upply Strike Back!
added.description: Cole and the Upply arrive at the Skull Sorcerer's keep in the hopes of rescuing Lloyd and the other ninja. But in order to do so, Cole will need to retrieve his mother's fabled swords, the Blades of Deliverance, which are hidden somewhere inside the keep!

added.title: The Son of Lilly
added.description: The battle for the fate of Shintaro Mountain concludes!

added.title: The Lady and the Queen/The AB's Silver Screen Debut
added.description: The Lady and the Queen: China Riot finds a new Bakugan: Barbetra. But this buzzy new Bakugan is a bit timid on the battleground. Riot takes her on as her new project to turn her into the battle queen she knows she can be./The AB's Silver Screen Debut: Lord Brakken and Duran have teamed up and are now the Bakugan film business. They look to the Awesome Brawlers for their expertise in both Bakugan culture and film making to get their movie made!

added.title: Nice to Meet You, Bakugan!/Magnus
added.description: Nice to Meet You, Bakugan!: After the Tiko incident, Bakugan brawling with a device has become extremely restricted. But there will always be people using devices to control Bakugan for evil. Magnus has taken it upon himself to step in and stop these villains and their wrongdoing./Magnus: After the Tiko incident, Bakugan brawling with a device has become extremely restricted. But there will always be people using devices to control Bakugan for evil. Magnus has taken it upon himself to step in and stop these villains and their wrongdoing.

added.title: The Bakugan Battle League/The Ancient Elder
added.description: The Bakugan Battle League: Benton Dusk is in the process of renovating a state of the art Bakugan Brawling stadium. When it comes to brawling, who better to test out the new arena than the Awesome Brawlers!/The Ancient Elder: Dan finds a new baku-bud in Gillitar. Well "bud" may be too strong a word, Dan and gang quickly learn that Gillator has a few "quirks" that keep him from fitting in with the rest of the Awesome Brawler's Bakugan.

added.title: Bakugan Wynton/The Boy from Brazil
added.description: Bakugan Wynton: Wynton has a new device that tracks down Bakugan! Right out of the gate the device works and, Wynton meets: Batrix. Like his name, Batrix is a little batty, and these two are certainly in for a "batty" first adventure./The Boy from Brazil: The Awesome Brawlers are off to a soccer match! In the process of doing so Shun discovers a new Bakugan friend, the boisterous Ramparian, and a new foe in Brazilian soccer star: Pepe.

added.title: Haunted House/Two of a Kind
added.description: Haunted House: Rumor has it that there's a haunted building in Los Volmos, and the Awesome Brawlers are on the case! Who doesn't like a good ghost hunt, plus capturing a ghost on camera should make Awesome Brawlers' next video a huge success!/Two of a Kind: Veronica Venegas is doing a special report on the Awesome brawlers own: Lightening! The special report takes a back seat when Lightening is challenged to a brawl. Lightening uses this brawl the perfect opportunity to rollout his new Bakugan partner: Tretorous.

added.title: Mi Guardaespaldas
added.description: Cuando Zombozo hipnotiza a toda la clase de panadería del abuelo Max, Ben y Gwen son los encargados de limpiar el desastre. Pero las cosas se complican aún más cuando Zombozo presenta a su nuevo guardaespaldas: iKevin 11!

added.title: Neumaticos de la Fortuna
added.description: Las compras en la tienda de segunda mano del equipo Tennyson se ven interrumpidas por el último atraco a alta velocidad de LaGrange -que ahora cuenta con la ayuda de un auto de carreras electromagnético superrápido- y Ben debe convencer a Kevin 11 para que ayude a detener la ola de robos del trotamundos endemoniado con la velocidad.

added.title: El Calor del Momento
added.description: Cuando Ben se deshace sin dificultad de los Climáticos, el equipo de Tennyson viaja a un centro de esquí para divertirse en la nieve. Pero cuando Ben se topa con los Climáticos una vez más, esta vez tendrá que vérselas con su fuerza iahora que Kevin 11 usó sus poderes de Bootleg para desbloquear sus controles emocionales!

added.title: Diagrama de Vin
added.description: Cuando Ben ve que Vin Etanol se asombra con los conocimientos automovilísticos de Kevin, los celos de Ben lo convencen de que tiene que superar a Kevin antes de que el joven convenza a Vin de adoptar su lado malo en una carrera a beneficio.

added.title: Una Situacion Pegajosa
added.description: Lo único que Ben quiere hacer es evitar que la Abeja Reina robe un banco, pero cuando Kevin aparece para intentar ser el héroe y quedarse con toda la gloria, Ben tiene que salvar a todos por segunda vez en el día o terminar embadurnado en miel.

added.title: Te Gustaria Entrar a Primer Imperio?
added.description: Mientras investigan un robo, los ninjas descubren Primer Imperio, un videojuego que  toma el control de todos los demás videojuegos de Ninjago.

added.title: Isla Dyer
added.description: Cuando los ninjas relacionan la desaparición de Jay con Primer Imperio, van a la Isla Dyer para buscar respuestas del diseñador del juego, Milton Dyer.

added.title: Deseo de Verano
added.description: Cuando Craig decide dejar una luciérnaga dentro de un frasco, termina interfiriendo con el delicado equilibrio del verano.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El Ascenso
added.description: Cole, los de abajo, la princesa Vania y Wu salen de la montaña para enfrentarse al malvado Hechicero Calavera.

added.title: Los de Arriba Contra Atacan
added.description: Cole y los de abajo llegan para rescatar a los Ninjas. Para ello, Cole tendrá que recuperar las espadas legendarias, las Espadas de la Liberación.

added.title: El Hijo de Lilly
added.description: iLa batalla por el destino de la Montaña Shintaro concluye!

added.title: Sin Cebollin
added.description: Manzana trata de sobrevivir un fin de semana solo mientras cuida la planta de Cebollín.

added.title: Noticias Unikitty
added.description: Estás viendo el programa de noticias del Unireino Super Good Morning Time Action Information Show, un programa de noticias variadas realizado (mal) por Unikitty y la banda: Hawkodile se encarga del clima, Puppycorn habla deportes, a pesar de no saber ninguna de las reglas, la Dra. Fox tiene un divertido segmento de cocina científica que sale mal, y Richard quiere que el programa deje de emitirse. Unikitty tiene un reportaje contundente y una gran primicia después de la pausa, isi el estudio sobrevive tanto tiempo!

added.title: Cena Festiva
added.description: Unikitty y Puppycorn están invitados al apartamento de Master Frown y Brock para una cena. Pero los dos compañeros de casa no logran ponerse de acuerdo absolutamente en nada. ¿Puede Unikitty ayudar a Brock y al Master Frown a volver a estar en armonía antes de que la cena sea un desastre? ¿Y descubrirá Puppycorn cuál es la puerta del baño?

added.title: Domingo de Flojos
added.description: Es domingo de pereza, iy Unikitty y Puppycorn la están pasando tan bien en el sofá que no quieren moverse nunca! Richard insiste en que tienen tareas por hacer, pero ellos no están dispuestos a dejar que termine el domingo de pereza. Los dos hacen todo lo posible para no salir nunca de la comodidad de su sofá, remando por el castillo como si estuvieran en un barco y reclutando a sus amigos para que abandonen sus tareas y se unan al domingo de pereza, isin importar qué tan peligroso e imposible puede llegar a ser!

added.title: Licencia para Golpear
added.description: A Hawkodile lo atrapa la policía de acción por trabajar como guardaespaldas sin licencia de acción. No puede proteger el reino ni hacer nada radical hasta tener la licencia, ipero la prueba en el Departamento de Caos y Violencia es para los nerds! Obligado a quitarse los guantes, Hawkodile lucha por vivir una vida sin golpes, por lo que Unikitty promete ayudar a su amigo a contener su impulso de entrar en acción y a estudiar para la prueba. Pero la prueba consiste en algo más de lo que parece.

added.title: Manzana es Bajito
added.description: Manzana tiene que ser alto para poder enamorarse.

added.title: Bichos
added.description: Cuando Unikitty y la banda descubren un bicho asqueroso en el castillo, están desesperados por deshacerse de él para siempre, pero Unikitty se niega a permitir que lo aplasten, no importa qué tan asqueroso o peligroso parezca. ¿Qué tipo de red está tejiendo Unikitty para sus amigos?

added.title: El chico del 3030
added.description: Los niños conocen a un misterioso niño del futuro y tratan de ayudarlo a completar su misión.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Buscando a Jessica
added.description: Jessica se adentra en un Arroyo desconocido, iy Craig debe encontrarla antes de que su madre se dé cuenta!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Apoca-piojos ahora
added.description: Cuando Chef pacta una tregua con los piojos seleccionando tres niños que los "alberguen" en sus cabezas, Courtney instiga una guerra de niños contra piojos.

added.title: Gno mas buen senor
added.description: Cuando  la guardería es invadida por gnomos malvados, Duncan se encuentra en el equipo equivocado.

added.title: Fuera de hora
added.description: Cuando las advertencias de Harold de no meterse con el reloj son ignoradas, los niños están obligados a salvarse a sí mismos cuando Duncan abre un agujero en la trama del tiempo.

added.title: Harold Matamoscas y el caliz de moscas
added.description: Después de descubrir lo que cree que es una varita mágica, Owen convierte accidentalmente a Harold en una mosca común.

added.title: Venganza apestosa
added.description: Cuando una mofeta viene a buscar su venganza anual contra el Chef, Duncan ve una oportunidad de tomarse unas vacaciones de la guardería.

added.title: Enfrenta Tus Miedos
added.description: Atrapados en una tienda de mascotas, Manzana y Cebollín deben enfrentarse a sus miedos para poder evitar que Papa Frita se enfrente a los suyos.

added.title: Revienta Fiestas
added.description: Los planes de la fiesta de Manzana y Cebollín son interrumpidos por un invitado malhumorado.

added.title: Teoria de Actitud Positiva
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín pasan un día en los zapatos de Falafel y usan su actitud positiva para demostrar que no debería estar tan malhumorado.

added.title: Grass is Greener
added.description: MOE wants to know what it's like to be a member of the Batwheels, but the bot gets more than he bargained for when Bam invites him along for an exciting mission to stop Poison Ivy.

added.title: Holidays on Ice
added.description: Frustrated by the Batwheels' holiday distractions, Batwing decides to "go solo" to thwart Mr. Freeze's evil Christmas-time plot. But Batwing soon realizes how hard it is to stop Mr. Freeze on her own!

added.title: Pinecone Palooza/The Big Footed Cave Bird
added.description: Grandma and Timmy are entering the Pinecone Art Show by carving a sculpture out of stone… that is, if they can learn how to carve./Ranger Nat is hiking and comes across the Big-Footed Cave Bird, and realizes it can't get back into her home.

added.title: Yip Yip Tree Tree/The Snowman Scarecrow
added.description: When the ornaments on the Pretty Big City tree break, the Mechas must build new ones and save the holidays for their friends./It's time for Zee and MacBarm's gift exchange, but the snowman scarecrow Zee made for MacBarm keeps blowing away!

added.title: The Mystery of Lookout Mountain
added.description: When cars go missing in the Mines, Thomas and Percy think they have a perfect adventure for the Biggest Adventure Club. But then they uncover that there was a similar problem at Lookout Mountain years ago. Thomas and friends set out to solve the two-headed mystery. Their search takes them under waterfalls, into unknown tunnels, new Crystal Caverns and ultimately brings the kids face to face with a mythical Mine Monster!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Something to Remember
added.description: On the last day of Yong Bao's visit to Sodor, his friends dig up a giant keepsake to help him remember them.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Sandy Versus the Storm
added.description: When a big storm approaches, Thomas and company must complete all a week's worth of deliveries by the end-of-the-workday whistle, but when Sandy needs repairs, Thomas and the gang will realize just how important Sandy is to the team!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: An UnbeLEAFable Day
added.description: While the trains are setting up for the Vicarstown Fall Festival, Thomas is feeling down about the end of summer and the changing weather.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Ghost Train
added.description: Percy has to deliver the mail on Halloween when everyone knows the legendary Ghost Train comes out! Thomas rolls along to help Percy face his fears, but when a "real" Ghost Train appears... things get almost spooky.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Monster Truck
added.description: Blippi wonders what makes a monster truck so special?

added.title: Bubbles
added.description: Blippi wonders how do you make bubbles?

added.title: Soggy Cereal
added.description: Blippi wonders why does cereal get soggy?

added.title: Sneeze
added.description: What is making Blippi sneeze? What makes anyone sneeze? Blippi shrinks down and flies up a nose to find out! A very mischievous piece of pollen demonstrates how to make a sneeze happen, resulting in Blippi himself getting blown away by a giant sneeze!

added.title: Snowflake
added.description: It's an icy day, and a very cold Blippi heads to the sky to find out how snowflakes are made. Way up high in the winter clouds he helps Mimi, an athletic dust particle, achieve her goal to build up enough ice crystals and transform into a unique and awesome snowflake. Way to be original Mimi!

added.title: Reading Fun
added.description: Ella takes out a book from the street library but Rishi is not too bothered. Ella shows him the amazing variety of stories that are available - he just has to find the one that's right for him. Rishi looks at books about cowboys, dragons, spaceships and fairy tales. Soon he is absolutely hooked!

added.title: Recycle Stomp
